      },
      "date": "2024-01-31 00:39:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThis obviously matches lots of things that cannot be IPv6 addresses, like with leading or trailing : or triple :, but I guess that doesn't matter anymore than the IPv4 pattern matching lots of other things.  Given that, I wonder why not just make it [0-9a-f:]+ like with the IPv4 pattern.\n\nDoes it matter that this doesn't matches uppercase A-F ??",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
